The six fundamental Principles
1. Love is the $input{&quot;only thing&quot;} that is intrinsically good.
2. Love is the $input{&quot;ruling&quot;} norm in ethical decision making and $input{&quot;replaces&quot;} all laws
3. Love and $input{&quot;justice&quot;} are the same, love is $input{&quot;justice&quot;} distributed
4. Love wills the $input{&quot;neighbours&quot;} good, regardless of whether the $input{&quot;neighbour&quot;} is liked.
5. Only the $input{&quot;end&quot;} justifies the $input{&quot;means&quot;}
